"{\"uid\": \"standardmedia.co.ke-sports-athletics-article-2001501482-diamond-league-olympic-champion-wanyonyi-moves-to-second-on-world-all-time-800m-list\", \"text\": \"Kenya's 20-year-old Olympic champion Emmanuel Wanyonyi delivered a standout performance at the Wanda Diamond League meeting in Lausanne on Thursday, where he clocked a blistering 1:41.11 in the men's 800m.This remarkable time catapulted Wanyonyi to joint second on the world all-time list, just 0.20 seconds shy of the world record of 1:40.91 set by his fellow Kenyan and role model, David Rudisha, at the London 2012 Olympics.Get Full Access for Ksh299/WeekUncover the stories others will not tell. Subscribe now for exclusive accessUnlock the Truth Now \\u300bUnlimited access to all premium contentUninterrupted ad-free browsing experienceMobile-optimized reading experienceWeekly NewslettersMPesa, Airtel Money and Cards acceptedAlready a subscriber?Log in  This remarkable time catapulted Wanyonyi to joint second on the world all-time list, just 0.20 seconds shy of the world record of 1:40.91 set by his fellow Kenyan and role model, David Rudisha, at the London 2012 Olympics.Get Full Access for Ksh299/WeekUncover the stories others will not tell. Subscribe now for exclusive accessUnlock the Truth Now \\u300bUnlimited access to all premium contentUninterrupted ad-free browsing experienceMobile-optimized reading experienceWeekly NewslettersMPesa, Airtel Money and Cards acceptedAlready a subscriber?Log in  Your experience on this site will be improved by allowing cookies.  Subscribe to our newsletter and stay updated on the latest developments and                     special offers!\"}"